<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Will pay for help in BB</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Gilorf">Gilorf</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:08 a.m. 1/7/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Will pay for help in BB<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/prexus.cgi?read=68" TARGET=_self>Re: Will pay for help in BB</A> (Tenen)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Well, your only chance really is to consent someone to loot your corpse and have them bring the stuff back up. This is because even though I can move around the basic gnolls (scrawny, patrolling, and gnolls) without them attacking me, if I were to escort a character at any lower level, they would still be targeted. In addition, if I ran into any burlies, guardsman, elites, or commanders, I would have my hands full.
<P>So as soon as a lower level character gets down there, the gnolls train like mad and there is nothing a higher level character can do about it (unless they are high enough to be immune to gnoll hits). I'm level 12 warrior, and the depths of BB are still dangerous - the only advantage is that I can run away from trouble easier.
<P>But back to the main point -- you have to be extremely careful to who you consent your corpse to. I don't think that I consent anyone. In which case your only option is to fall down the tree again and try to sneak past them. I did this when I fell down the tree (it took a couple of times) and I think I ended up just dying in a place where it was easier for me to get my corpse.
<P>But someone consented me yesterday and I helped them, but they made it a little outside of the dangerous area. If I was on at the same time as you, I would gladly help, but I am only on in the evenings.
<P>&gt; I would forget about it,I did the exact same
<BR>&gt; thing with my lvl 7 barbarian warrior,I got
<BR>&gt; someone to help and we both died,its a lost
<BR>&gt; cause trying to go down after your corpse.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
